n%20announced%20a%20successful%20test%20of%20an%20experimental%20nuclear-powered%20cruise%20missile%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20Burvestnik%20was%20unveiled%20in%202018%20as%20a%20unique%20missile%20with%20a%20theoretically%20unlimited%20flight%20range.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIf%20it%20works%2C%20the%20weapon's%20utility%20is%20debatable%2C%20and%20a%20nuclear%20weapons%20expert%20said%20it's%20likely%20for%20political%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20claims%20his%20experimental%20nuclear-powered%20cruise%20missile%20works%2C%20but%20even%20if%20that%20is%20true%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20as%20much%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20weapon%26quot%3B%20as%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapon%20isn't%20much%20of%20an%20addition%20beyond%20the%20nuclear%20strike%20options%20Russia%20already%20has%20in%20its%20arsenal%2C%20a%20nuclear%20weapons%20expert%20told%20Insider.%20That%20said%2C%20the%20missile%20isn't%20useless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-tested-nuclear-powered-cruise-missile-apparently-successful-putin-2023-10%5C%22%3Eannounced%20that%20Russia%20conducted%20a%20successful%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%209M730%20Burevestnik%20missile%2C%20one%20of%20six%20new%20strategic%20weapons%20he%20revealed%20in%202018%20that%20Russia%20was%20developing.%20In%20his%20most%20recent%20announcement%2C%20he%20didn't%20elaborate%20further%20on%20the%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20reporting%20indicates%20that%20Russia%20conducted%20just%20over%20a%20dozen%20tests%20between%202017%20and%202019.%20None%20were%20successful%2C%20though%20one%20or%20two%20may%20have%20been%20promising.%20During%20the%20course%20of%20testing%2C%20the%20retrieval%20of%20a%20weapon%20that%20previously%20crashed%20into%20the%20sea%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffailed-test-of-putins-new-missile-may-have-caused-explosion-2019-8%5C%22%3Edeadly%20nuclear%20accident%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%2C%20exactly%2C%20the%20strongest%20track%20record%2C%20but%20if%20Putin's%20claims%20are%20true%20and%20the%20weapon%20is%20at%20last%20showing%20promise%2C%20that%20raises%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20follow-up%20questions%20about%20the%20potential%20functions%20and%20utility%20of%20the%20Burevestnik.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tests%20of%20a%20cruise%20missile%20with%20a%20Burevestnik%20nuclear%20engine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ef0849f7ca8b2bbda8d96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETests%20of%20a%20cruise%20missile%20with%20a%20Burevestnik%20nuclear%20engine.%3Cp%3ERIA%20Novosti%20%2F%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWill%20the%20%26quot%3Blow-flying%2C%20stealth%20cruise%20missile%20with%20a%20nuclear%20warhead%26quot%3B%20be%20able%20to%20operate%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20practically%20unlimited%20range%26quot%3B%20along%20an%20%26quot%3Bunpredictable%20flight%20path%26quot%3B%20as%20Putin%20described%20it%20in%202018%3F%20Will%20it%20have%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ability%20to%20bypass%20interception%20lines%26quot%3B%20and%20be%20%26quot%3Binvulnerable%20to%20all%20existing%20and%20future%20missile%20defense%20and%20air%20defense%20systems%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20has%20claimed%3F%20It%20is%20not%20entirely%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20Burevestnik%20in%20the%20news%2C%20let%20me%20say%20it%20again%20%E2%80%94%20the%20utility%20of%20this%20weapon%20system%20(assuming%20it%20works)%20is%20about%20zero%2C%26quot%3B%20nuclear%20weapons%20expert%20Pavel%20Podvig%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Frussianforces%2Fstatus%2F1709998391315300410%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eposted%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20shortly%20after%20news%20broke%20of%20Putin's%20announcement%20on%20October%205.%20He%20later%20told%20Insider%20%26quot%3Bit%20doesn't%20offer%20any%20advantages%20over%20the%20existing%20strategic%20systems%26quot%3B%20Russia%20already%20possesses%2C%20like%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missiles%20(ICBMs)%20and%20submarine-launched%20ballistic%20missiles%20(SLBMs).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssuming%20that%20it%20works%20as%20advertised%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20very%20long-range%20cruise%20missile%2C%26quot%3B%20Podvig%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20weapon%20couldn't%20have%20some%20use%2C%20especially%20politically.%20And%20in%20a%20time%20when%20Ukrainian%20offensive%20efforts%20are%20slowly%20but%20steadily%20chipping%20away%20at%20Russia's%20defenses%20and%20Moscow%20continues%20throwing%20waves%20of%20its%20troops%20from%20dwindling%20reserves%20at%20the%20battlefield%2C%20Putin%20may%20also%20see%20the%20weapon%20as%20a%20bargaining%20chip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Putin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651fddda9f7ca8b2bbdb6a54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20speaks%20during%20his%20annual%20meeting%20with%20participants%20of%20the%20Valdai%20Discussion%20Club%20on%20October%205%2C%202023%20in%20Sochi%2C%20Russia.%3Cp%3EContributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Burevestnik%20is%20one%20of%20Russia's%20six%20strategic%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20weapons%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20are%20sometimes%20called.%20The%20systems%20are%20in%20various%20stages%20of%20development%2C%20with%20some%20already%20in%20service%20with%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20are%20unproven%20while%20others%20haven't%20lived%20up%20to%20the%20hype.%20Among%20the%20other%20missiles%20in%20the%20mix%2C%20the%203M22%20Zircon%20anti-ship%20hypersonic%20cruise%20missile%2C%20currently%20deployed%20with%20the%20Russian%20Navy%2C%20is%20still%20something%20of%20a%20question%20mark%20like%20the%20RS-28%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20that%20was%20recently%20put%20in%20service%2C%20but%20the%20supposedly%20unbeatable%20Kh-47M2%20Kinzhal%20air-launched%20ballistic%20missiles%20was%20defeated%20by%20US-provided%20Patriot%20air%20defense%20batteries%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Burevestnik%2C%20which%20means%20%26quot%3BAnnouncer%20of%20the%20Storm%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20one%20of%20the%20more%20experimental%20systems%20alongside%20its%20underwater%20counterpart%2C%20the%20Poseidon%20torpedo%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20in%20the%20world%20has%20anything%20like%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Putin%20said%20in%202018.%20That's%20true%2C%20although%20US%20scientists%20had%20efforts%20to%20develop%20something%20similar%20decades%20ago%20and%20gave%20up%20because%20the%20concept%20is%2C%20as%20one%20arms%20control%20expert%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20technical%2C%20strategic%2C%20and%20environmental%20nightmare.%26quot%3B%C2%A0Technology%20has%20improved%20since%20those%20efforts%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20kind%20of%20skeptical%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20mission%20of%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Podvig%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20if%20you%20look%20at%20missile%20defenses%20and%20standard%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20normal%20ballistic%20missiles.%20They%20are%20definitely%20capable%20of%20penetrating%20any%20missile%20defenses.%26quot%3B%C2%A0Many%20modern%20ballistic%20missiles%20are%20designed%20with%20countermeasures%20to%20fool%20defenses%2C%20which%20may%20be%20less%20effective%20than%20advertised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20claims%20the%20Burevestnik%2C%20as%20a%20nuclear-powered%20system%2C%20can%20effectively%20fly%20for%20an%20unlimited%20amount%20of%20time%20and%20range%2C%20and%20can%20be%20sent%20to%20any%20target%20at%20a%20moment's%20notice.%20The%20missile%2C%20essentially%20a%20very-long%20range%20cruise%20missile%2C%20can't%20be%20intercepted%20by%20missile%20defense%20systems%20that%20are%20designed%20to%20counter%20ICBMs%2C%20meaning%20it%20could%20theoretically%20penetrate%20key%20enemy%20air%20defenses%20to%20strike%20its%20target.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20a%20missile%20defense%20system%20likely%20would%20not%20protect%20against%20all%20incoming%20ICBMs%2C%20Podvig%20noted%2C%20as%20some%20warheads%20would%20likely%20overwhelm%20and%20break%20through%20and%20some%20missiles%20would%20come%20with%20decoys%20and%20penetration%20aids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Burevestnik%20simply%20offers%20additional%20strike%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20capability%20Russia%20has%20sought%20with%20its%20development%20of%20the%20Burevestnik%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20controversial%20US%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20Anti-Ballistic%20Missile%20Treaty%20with%20Russia%20in%202002.%20The%20agreement%20was%20designed%20to%20limit%20the%20use%20anti-ballistic%20missile%20systems%20intended%20to%20defend%20against%20nuclear%20attacks.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%20pulled%20out%20so%20the%20US%20could%20develop%20the%20National%20Missile%20Defense%20system%2C%20but%20the%20move%20led%20to%20Russia%20bolstering%20its%20nuclear%20capabilities%20and%20defense%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20and%20ultimately%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20new%20Burevestnik.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20weapon's%20gotten%20plenty%20of%20US%20attention%20since%20its%20initial%20testing%2C%20and%20that%20makes%20it%20and%20potential%20launch%20facilities%20%E2%80%94%20which%20appear%20to%20be%20rather%20large%20and%20vulnerable%20%E2%80%94%20targets%20if%20there%20were%20ever%20a%20conflict%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20imagine%20that%20if%20it%20ever%20comes%20to%20that%2C%20if%20this%20thing%20is%20ever%20deployed%2C%20then%20these%20