ps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f6900e88f76900192ce869%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERising%20levels%20of%20anxiety%20among%20Gen%20Z%20may%20be%20connected%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20location%20tracking%20apps.%20%3Cp%3EAdam%20Berry%2FRedferns%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGen%20Z%20seems%20OK%20with%20their%20parents%20using%20location%20sharing%20apps%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20them.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESafety%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20main%20benefit%20of%20sharing%20your%20location%20with%20others%20at%20all%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERising%20levels%20of%20anxiety%20among%20young%20people%20may%20be%20driving%20the%20embrace%20of%20location%20apps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20popularity%20of%20location%20tracking%20apps%20such%20as%20Life360%20suggests%20that%20young%20people%20are%20increasingly%20happy%20for%20their%20parents%20to%20be%20able%20to%20see%20where%20they%20are%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDownloads%20of%20Life360%20doubled%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20with%20one%20in%20nine%20US%20families%20%E2%80%93%2033%20million%20%E2%80%93%20now%20using%20the%20app%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fpersonal-tech%2Ftrack-my-phone-teens-feel-safer-when-parents-monitor-7ad437ff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20apps%20such%20as%20Google's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffamilies.google%2Ffamilylink%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFamily%20Link%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Apple's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Ffind-my%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFind%20My%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20being%20used%20by%20Gen%20Z%20to%20share%20their%20location%20with%20parents%20and%20friends%20while%20they%20travel%20to%20school%2C%20drive%20%E2%80%93%20or%20even%20during%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20tools%20can%20also%20send%20alerts%20for%20events%20such%20as%20car%20crashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocation%20tracking%20can%20be%20turned%20off%20and%20on%20so%20that%20a%20user%20can%20maintain%20privacy%20when%20they%20want%20it%2C%20but%20according%20to%20a%202022%20survey%20carried%20out%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheharrispoll.com%2Fbriefs%2Flocation-sharing-features%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Harris%20Poll%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2016%25%20of%20US%20adults%20have%20the%20setting%20activated%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.life360.com%2Fblog%2Fgen-z-location-sharing-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201%2C200%20adults%20conducted%20by%20Life360%20found%20%3Cspan%3E54%25%20of%20respondents%20thought%20it%20necessary%20or%20usually%20appropriate%20for%20parents%20to%20ask%20their%20children%20to%20share%20their%20location%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20embrace%20of%20location%20tracking%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20related%20to%20rising%20levels%20of%20anxiety%20among%20younger%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20turbulence%20of%20Gen%20Z's%20adolescence%20spawned%20a%20mental%20health%20crisis%20that%20was%20only%20amplified%20by%20the%20pandemic%2C%20social%20media%2C%20and%20the%2024-hour%20news%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Michele%20Borba%2C%20a%20educational%20psychologist%20and%20spokesperson%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.life360.com%2Fblog%2Fgen-z-location-sharing-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELife360%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20uncertain%20times%2C%20this%20generation%20has%20come%20to%20crave%20the%20added%20layer%20of%20security%20that%20location%20sharing%20provides%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELife360's%20survey%20found%2094%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20saw%20the%20benefits%20of%20location%20sharing%2C%20with%20more%20than%20half%20regarding%20such%20apps%20as%20being%20s