%20Build%20Infrastructure%20Along%20LAC%2C%20Border%20with%20Bhutan%3A%20Pentagon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F17115001%2FIndustry-Conflict-Politics-China-India-Flags-5628865.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20China%20has%20continued%20to%20develop%20infrastructure%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20with%20India%2C%20including%20new%20roads%2C%20helipads%2C%20a%20bridge%20and%20an%20airport%2C%20and%20new%20villages%20in%20disputed%20area%20in%20neighbouring%20Bhutan%2C%20stated%20the%20Pentagon%E2%80%99s%20annual%20report%20on%20Chinese%20military%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReleased%20last%20week%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F19%2F2003323409%2F-1%2F-1%2F1%2F2023-MILITARY-AND-SECURITY-DEVELOPMENTS-INVOLVING-THE-PEOPLES-REPUBLIC-OF-CHINA.PDF%5C%22%3E2023%20Annual%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Congress%3A%20Military%20and%20Security%20Developments%20Involving%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20of%20China%2C%20said%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20Peoples%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20%E2%80%9Chas%20maintained%20continuous%20force%20presence%20and%20continued%20infrastructure%20build%20up%20along%20the%20LAC%E2%80%9D%20after%20the%20clash%20between%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20force%20at%20Galwan%20valley%20in%20June%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EListing%20the%20Chinese%20developments%20on%20its%20borders%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20the%20report%20noted%20that%20in%202022%2C%20%E2%80%9CChina%20continued%20to%20develop%20military%20infrastructure%20along%20the%20LAC.%20These%20improvements%20include%20underground%20storage%20facilities%20near%20Doklam%2C%20new%20roads%20in%20all%20three%C2%A0sectors%20of%20the%20LAC%2C%20new%20villages%20in%20disputed%20areas%20in%20neighboring%20Bhutan%2C%20a%20second%20bridge%20over%20Pangong%20Lake%2C%20a%20dual-purpose%20airport%20near%20the%20center%20sector%2C%20and%20multiple%20helipads.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20report%20also%20said%20that%20China%20had%20increased%20manpower%20deployment%20along%20the%20border.%20%E2%80%9CIn%202022%2C%20China%20deployed%20one%20border%20regiment%2C%20supported%20by%20two%20divisions%20of%20Xinjiang%20and%20Tibet%20Military%20Districts%20with%20four%20combined%20arms%20brigades%20(CAB)%20in%20reserve%20in%20the%20western%20sector%20of%20the%20LAC.%20China%20also%20deployed%20as%20many%20as%20three%20light-to-medium%20CABs%20in%20the%20eastern%20sector%20from%20other%20theater%20commands%20and%20an%20additional%20three%20CABs%20in%20the%20central%20sector%20of%20the%20LAC.%20Although%20some%20elements%20of%20a%20light%20CAB%20eventually%20withdrew%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20deployed%20forces%20remain%20in%20place%20along%20the%20LAC%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%20have%20been%20at%20a%20stand-off%20since%20April-May%202020%20at%20multiple%20points%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20along%20the%20LAC.%20The%20crisis%20escalated%20when%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20clashed%20in%20a%20hand-to-hand%20fight%20in%20Galwan%20valley%20resulting%20in%20the%20death%20of%20at%20least%2024%20soldiers.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20fatal%20fight%20at%20the%20LAC%20in%20four%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20both%20sides%20have%20met%20in%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20military-level%20and%20foreign%20office-led%20talks.%20There%20has%20been%20withdrawal%20of%20troops%20by%20both%20India%20and%20China%20at%20around%20four%20friction%20points%2C%20the%20latest%20being%20at%20Gogra-Hotsprings%20last%20year.%20However%2C%20the%20remaining%20points%20at%20Demchok%20and%20Depsang%20Springs%20are%20proving%20harder%20to%20reach%20a%20compromise%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20China%20was%20overtaking%20previous%20projects%20on%20building%20up%20its%20nuclear%20weapons%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202020%20report%2C%20the%20US%20defence%20department%20had%20estimated%20that%20China%20would%20double%20its%20nuclear%20warhead%20arsenal%20which%20was%20in%20the%20low-200s%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20Beijing%20has%20accelerated%20its%20nuclear%20expansion%2C%20and%20DoD%20estimates%20China%E2%80%99s%20stockpile%20had%20more%20than%20500%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20as%20of%20May%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Pentagon.%20The%20latest%20projection%20is%20that%20China%20will%20have%20over%201%2C000%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20China%20has%20%E2%80%9Calmost%20certainly%E2%80%9D%20learnt%20lessons%20from%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20which%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20applicable%20to%20the%20PRC%E2%80%99s%20goal%20of%20strengthening%20its%20whole-of-government%20approach%20to%20countering%20a%20perceived%20U.S.-led%20containment%20strategy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWestern%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20almost%20certainly%20have%20amplified%20the%20PRC%E2%80%99s%20push%20for%20defense%20and%20technological%20self-sufficiency%20and%20financial%20resilience%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20observed%20that%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20major%2C%20unexpected%20challenge%E2%80%9D%20for%20China.%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20multiple%20warnings%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20intentions%20towards%20Kyiv%2C%20Beijing%20was%20caught%20completely%20off%20guard%20by%20the%20full%20scope%20and%20scale%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20China%20has%20taken%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdiscreet%2C%20flexible%2C%20and%20cautious%20approach%E2%80%9D%20in%20providing%20material%20support%20to%20Russia.%20%E2%80%9CPRC%20leaders%20and%20officials%20have%20sought%20to%20deflect%20international%20criticism%20over%20Sino-Russian%20relations%20and%20protect%20its%20international%20reputation%20by%20using%20high-level%20diplomatic%20engagements%20and%20messaging%20emphasizing%20the%20PRC%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cneutral%E2%80%9D%20role%20in%20the%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697973042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F17115001%2FIndustry-Conflict-Politics-China-India-Flags-5628865.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-is-continuing-to-build-infrastructure-along-lac-border-with-bhutan-pentagon%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20has%20continued%20to%20develop%20infrastructure%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20with%20India%2C%20including%20new%20roads%2C%20helipads%2C%20a%20bridge%20and%20an%20airport%2C%20and%20new%20villages%20in%20disputed%20area%20in%20neighbouring%20Bhutan%2C%20stated%20the%20Pentagon%E2%80%99s%20annual%20report%20on%20Chinese%20military%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-is-continuing-to-build-infrastructure-along-lac-border-with-bhutan-pentagon%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Venezuela%20opposition%20holds%20primary%20to%20pick%20unity%20candidate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697972484000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F8CD9%2Fproduction%2F_131475063_db0cb509cb72abe7f817edf81569e75afee5c5830_0_6000_40001000x667.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67156228%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Opposition%20groups%20aim%20to%20pick%20one%20figure%20to%20take%20on%20the%20government's%20candidate%20in%20the%202024%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67156228%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2