t%20started%20off%20as%20a%20weekly%2C%20the%20newspaper%20turned%20into%20a%20daily%20in%201819.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20going%20through%20the%20digitised%20files%20of%20the%20newspaper%20during%20my%20Ph.D.%20fieldwork%20at%20the%20newspaper%20section%20of%20the%20British%20Library%20in%20London%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20acknowledged%20the%20significance%20of%20sports%20reporting%20quite%20early%20and%20published%20a%20dedicated%20column%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Sporting%20Gazettee%E2%80%99%2C%20once%20a%20week.%20Besides%20reporting%20weekly%20races%2C%20the%20column%20also%20gave%20equal%20weight%20to%20cricket%20matches.%20By%20the%201850s%2C%20along%20with%20detailed%20match%20reports%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20also%20reproducing%20full-length%20scorecards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20these%20scorecards%20only%20had%20European%20names%3B%20however%2C%20one%20report%20published%20on%20January%205%2C%201857%2C%20stood%20out%20for%20the%20significant%20presence%20of%20Indians%20in%20the%20match%20report.%20The%20match%20played%20at%20the%20suburban%20town%20of%20Chinsurah%20in%20the%20Bengal%20Province%20in%201856%20interestingly%20pitted%20a%20group%20of%20Bengali%20students%20from%20Krishnagar%20against%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%2C%20an%20army%20regiment%20that%20was%20in%20action%20during%20the%20great%20revolt%20of%201857%2C%20on%20the%20cricket%20pitch.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20313px)%2085vw%2C%20313px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20225559%2Fscorecard.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22313%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20225559%2Fscorecard.png%20239w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20225559%2Fscorecard-127x300.png%20127w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681097%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMatch%20Scorecard%20Courtesy%3A%20The%20British%20Library.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ECompetitive%20cricket%20has%20been%20played%20in%20Bengal%20since%20the%2018th%20century.%20The%20earliest%20surviving%20reference%20to%20the%20Calcutta%20Cricket%20Club%20goes%20back%20to%201780.%20The%20Calcutta%20Cricket%20Club%20played%20annual%20fixtures%20against%20various%20regiments%20of%20the%20army%20stationed%20either%20at%20Fort%20William%20or%20the%20cantonment%20at%20Barrackpore.%20The%20various%20match%20reports%20published%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20suggest%20regular%20fixtures%20were%20also%20played%20between%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Calcutta%20Cricket%20Club%20and%20combined%20elevens%20featuring%20alumni%20of%20different%20British%20educational%20institutions%2C%20like%20the%20Etonians%20and%20Harrovians%20or%20the%20Universities%20of%20Oxford%20and%20Cambridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%20%3C%2Fem%3Eeven%20provides%20us%20with%20reports%20of%20unusual%20contests%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98Married%E2%80%99%20vs%20%E2%80%98Single%E2%80%99.%20A%20match%20the%20unmarrieds%20won%20comprehensively%20by%2010%20wickets.%20But%20these%20match%20reports%20say%20very%20little%20about%20the%20participation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98natives%E2%80%99.%20We%20do%20find%20a%20report%20of%20a%20match%20played%20between%20the%20Calcutta%20Cricket%20Club%20and%20the%20Medical%20College%20in%20January%201856.%20But%20the%20names%20of%20the%20players%20on%20the%20Medical%20College%20team%20suggest%20either%20they%20were%20Eurasians%20or%20Europeans.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20brevity%20of%20the%20report%20also%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20speculate%20if%20the%20Medical%20College%20team%20was%20represented%20by%20the%20students%20of%20the%20college%20or%20the%20staff.%20One%20can%20argue%20that%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bengal%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20newspaper%20that%20catered%20mostly%20to%20the%20European%20population%20of%20the%20city%2C%20preferred%20to%20overlook%20the%20sporting%20exploits%20of%20the%20Indians.%20There%20are%20historical%20sources%20that%20indicate%20that%20by%20the%201840s%2C%20the%20Indian%20sepoys%20were%20picking%20up%20the%20game%20of%20cricket%20and%20often%20found%20their%20way%20into%20the%20regimental%20teams.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20very%20little%20information%20on%20the%20early%20participation%20of%20civilians.%20Due%20to%20the%20dearth%20of%20source%20materials%2C%20this%20report%20of%20the%20match%20played%20at%20Chinsurah%20becomes%20all%20the%20more%20important%20for%20enthusiasts%20of%20Indian%20cricket%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERise%20of%20cricket%20in%20Bengal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Bombay%2C%20where%20the%20Parsi%20mercantile%20class%20took%20the%20initiative%2C%20in%20Bengal%20it%20was%20the%20middle%20class%20that%20took%20the%20lead%20in%20popularising%20the%20game.%20Participation%20in%20bodily%20activities%20and%20European%20sports%20was%20propelled%20by%20the%20impulse%20to%20counter%20the%20colonial%20aspersions%20of%20effeminacy%20and%20physical%20inferiority.%20For%20the%20locals%2C%20involvement%20in%20the%20game%20of%20cricket%20took%20on%20a%20more%20organised%20form%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20pioneering%20figures%20like%20Nagendraprasad%20Sarbadhikary%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20Boys%20Club%20at%20Calcutta%20in%201880.%20In%20the%20town%20of%20Dhaka%2C%20we%20find%20the%20report%20of%20a%20cricket%20match%20where%2016%20Bengalis%20competed%20against%2011%20Europeans%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20great%20popular%20support%20in%201876.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20even%20more%20interesting%20description%20of%20how%20the%20game%20was%20played%20in%20Calcutta%20in%20the%201870s%20can%20be%20found%20in%20Mahendranath%20Dutta%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20of%20his%20elder%20brother%2C%20Swami%20Vivekananda.%20Dutta%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6.%20bricks%20were%20piled%20up%20on%20top%20of%20one%20other.%20A%20person%20with%20a%20bat%20guarded%20the%20pile%20of%20bricks%2C%20which%20served%20as%20the%20wicket%2C%20from%20the%20bowler.%20If%20the%20bowler%20managed%20to%20hit%20the%20pile%20of%20bricks%2C%20the%20batsman%20was%20out%E2%80%A6The%20game%20required%20one%20to%20be%20skilled%20and%20alert.%20Vireswar%20showed%20much%20enthusiasm%20for%20the%20game%20of%20cricket%E2%80%A6.%20A%20number%20of%20kids%20from%20the%20neighbourhood%20congregated%20in%20the%20courtyard%20each%20afternoon%20to%20play%20cricket.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDutta%E2%80%99s%20description%20of%20the%20game%20is%20very%20much%20akin%20to%20how%20the%20game%20is%20played%20today%20across%20neighbourhoods%20in%20the%20subcontinent.%20The%20description%20also%20underlines%20that%20by%20the%201870s%2C%20the%20game%20of%20cricket%20was%20popular%20enough%20in%20Calcutta%20to%20be%20played%20by%20middle-class%20children%20with%20makeshift%20arrangements%20like%20piled-up%20brick%20wickets.%3Cem%3E%20The%20Hurkaru%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereport%20on%20the%20match%20involving%20the%20college%20team%20from%20Krishnanagar%20and%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20in%201856%20also%20substantiates%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20little%20information%20that%20we%20can%20gather%20from%20the%20report%2C%20we%20can%20infer%20that%20cricket%20was%20already%20quite%20common%20among%20college%20students%20in%20Bengal%20by%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20At%20least%20two%20suburban%20colleges%2C%20those%20of%20Hooghly%20and%20Krishnanagar%2C%20had%20their%20own%20cricket%20teams%20in%201856%2C%20which%20was%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20before%20official%20initiatives%20were%20taken%20to%20incorporate%20sports%20in%20the%20curriculum%20of%20educational%20institutions%20in%20the%20province%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20Sir%20George%20Campbell%2C%20the%20Lieutenant-Governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20match%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20match%20begins%20with%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20landing%20at%20the%20town%20of%20Chinsurah%20after%20a%20long%20voyage%20from%20Britain%20on%20the%20final%20week%20of%20the%20year%20in%201856.%20Located%20about%2060%20km%20upstream%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20Chinsurah%20was%20a%20Dutch%20settlement%20from%201656.%20The%20town%20came%20under%20British%20control%20in%201825%20when%20the%20Dutch%20ceded%20much%20of%20their%20settlements%20in%20India%20in%20exchange%20for%20Sumatra.%20Most%20British%20regiments%20shipped%20to%20India%20for%20the%20service%20of%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20generally%20landed%20on%20Chinsurah%2C%20which%20was%20the%20northernmost%20deep-water%20anchorage%20on%20River%20Hooghly.%20The%20regiment%20was%20then%20stationed%20briefly%20at%20the%20army%20barracks%20in%20Chinsurah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21221932%2FThe_barracks_at_Hooghly.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22712%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21221932%2FThe_barracks_at_Hooghly.jpg%20712w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21221932%2FThe_barracks_at_Hooghly-300x228.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681224%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20barracks%20at%20Hooghly.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FFrederick%20Fiebig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20imposing%20army%20barracks%20of%20Chinsurah%2C%20which%20currently%20house%20the%20District%20Court%20of%20Hooghly%20and%20other%20governmental%20offices%2C%20are%20among%20the%20longest%20buildings%20in%20Bengal.%20The%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20disembarked%20on%20Chinsurah%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20before%20the%20cricket%20match%2C%20where%20they%20remained%20for%20a%20brief%20period%20before%20being%20sent%20off%20to%20Allahabad%20on%20barges%20along%20the%20Ganges.%20From%20Allahabad%2C%20the%20members%20of%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20marched%20along%20the%20Grand%20Trunk%20Road%20to%20Meerut%2C%20which%20they%20reached%20on%20March%2011%2C%201857.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20their%20time%20in%20Chinsurah%2C%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20were%20invited%20to%20play%20a%20cricket%20match%20with%20the%20locals.%20Curiously%2C%20the%20team%20that%20was%20asked%20to%20play%20the%20army%20regiment%20was%20neither%20another%20division%20of%20the%20army%20nor%20a%20European%20club%2C%20but%20rather%20a%20bunch%20of%20young%20college%20students.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20that%20these%20%E2%80%98Collegians%E2%80%99%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98natives%E2%80%99%20of%20Chinsurah.%20Due%20to%20the%20unavailability%20of%20the%20students%20from%20Hooghly%20College%2C%20the%20students%20of%20the%20college%20in%20Krishnanagar%2C%20located%20about%2090%20km%20away%2C%20were%20brought%20in.%20It%20is%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20college%20team%20that%20is%20of%20particular%20interest%20to%20us.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hurkaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98Collegians%E2%80%99%20were%20represented%20by%20three%20Europeans%20or%20Eurasians%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20were%20all%20Bengalis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20group%20of%20Indians%20were%20facing%20a%20British%20army%20regiment%20on%20the%20field%20of%20sports%2C%20what%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20underlined%20is%20the%20decision%20to%20field%20a%20composite%20team.%20This%20was%20long%20before%20cricket%20teams%20were%20to%20be%20divided%20along%20racial%20and%20communal%20lines%20in%20the%20famous%20Bombay%20Quadrangular.%20R.%20Thwaytes%2C%20G.%20Beatson%2C%20and%20H.%20A.%20Graves%20took%20the%20field%20along%20with%20Ram%20Coomar%20Mookerjea%20and%20Hurroprashad%20Ghose.%20Gobind%20Chunder%20Mookerjea%2C%20Chunderkant%20Roy%2C%20Ishar%20Chunder%20Roy%2C%20Koylash%20Chunder%20Roy%2C%20Shoshee%20B%20Banerjea%2C%20and%20Kistonath%20Roy%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20December%2031%2C%201856.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20inexperienced%20%E2%80%98Collegians%E2%80%99%20did%20put%20up%20a%20stiff%20resistance%20against%20the%206th%C2%A0Dragoon%20Guards.%20Batting%20first%2C%20the%20army%20team%20folded%20out%20for%20just%2066%20runs.%20Graves%20picked%20up%20five%20wickets%2C%20while%20Ram%20Coomar%20Mookerjea%20chipped%20in%20with%20four%20wickets.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Collegians%E2%80%99%20could%20manage%20only%2023%20runs%20with%20the%20bat.%20The%20students%20from%20the%20town%20of%20Krishnanagar%20fought%20back%20in%20the%20third%20innings%2C%20bowling%20out%20the%20Dragoon%20Guards%20for%20just%2042%20runs.%20Graves%20again%20was%20the%20pick%20of%20the%20bowlers%2C%20capturing%20three%20wickets%2C%20while%20Mookerjea%20managed%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20innings%20of%20the%20match%2C%20with%2085%20runs%20to%20win%2C%20the%20Collegians%20put%20up%20a%20commendable%20fight.%20Opening%20the%20batting%2C%20Thwaytes%20scored%2024%20and%20Ishar%20Chunder%20Roy%20battled%20on%20till%20the%20very%20end%2C%20scoring%2021.%20The%20%E2%80%98Collegians%E2%80%99%20were%20pipped%20at%20the%20post%20in%2084.%20They%20lost%20the%20match%20by%20just%20one%20run.%20The%20report%20says%20there%20were%20frequent%20cheers%20from%20the%20crowd%2C%20particularly%20for%20Ram%20Coomar%20Mookerjea.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20follow%20up%20on%20the%20subsequent%20careers%20of%20the%20Indian%20students%20who%20took%20part%20in%20the%20match.%20But%20we%20are%20a%20bit%20more%20lucky%20with%20their%20opponents%3B%20all%20the%20members%20of%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%20were%20posted%20in%20the%20various%20cantonments%20across%20Northern%20India%20when%20the%20great%20revolt%20of%201857%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Lieutenant%20(Sir)%20Baker%20Creed%20Russell%2C%20who%20opened%20the%20innings%20for%20the%20Dragoon%20Guards%20and%20picked%20up%20seven%20wickets%20in%20the%20match%2C%20was%20stationed%20at%20Meerut%20on%20the%20fateful%20day%20of%20May%2010%2C%201857.%20Russell%20later%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20recapturing%20Bareilly%20and%20Shahjahanpur%20from%20the%20sepoys.%20Russell%20was%20even%20awarded%20a%20medal%20for%20his%20part%20in%20capturing%20Tantiya%20Tope.%20The%20news%20report%2C%20though%2C%20is%20significant%20to%20the%20aficionados%20of%20sports%20or%20cricket%20history%20not%20because%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98heroes%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98mutiny%E2%80%99%20but%20for%20the%20Indian%20students%20who%20fought%20them%20on%20the%20twenty-two%20yards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESarbajit%20Mitra%20completed%20his%20PhD%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20History%20at%20SOAS%20University%20of%20London%20in%202023.%20Sarbajit%E2%80%99s%20doctoral%20research%20focuses%20on%20the%20socio-medical%20history%20of%20intoxicants%20in%20colonial%20Bengal%20in%20the%20nineteenth%20century.%20Currently%2C%20he%20is%20a%20faculty%20member%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20History%20at%20St.%20Xavier%E2%80%99s%20College%2C%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697951831000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20230251%2F1200px-Ground_of_Calcutta_Cricket_Club_15th_Jany_1861_-_Percy_Carpenter.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fa-cricket-match-in-bengals-chinsurah-and-its-fascinating-connection-to-the-1857-revolt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20match%20played%20at%20the%20suburban%20town%20of%20Chinsurah%20in%20the%20Bengal%20Province%20in%201856%20pitted%20a%20group%20of%20Bengali%20students%20from%20Krishnagar%20against%20the%206th%20Dragoon%20Guards%2C%20an%20army%20regiment%20that%20was%20in%20action%20during%20the%20great%20revolt%20of%201857%2C%20on%20the%20cricket%20pitch.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A65%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fa-cricket-match-in-bengals-chinsurah-and-its-fascinating-connection-to-the-1857-revolt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saudi%20Prince's%20Takedown%20Of%20Israel%2C%20Hamas%20Over%20Gaza%20War%20Mentions%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20powerful%20remarks%20on%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20a%20Saudi%20Arabia%20prince%2C%20who%20was%20the%20country's%20former%20intelligence%20chief%2C%20has%20slammed%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%20and%20said%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bno%20heroes%20in%20this%20conflict%2C%20only%20victims%26quot%3B.%20Turki%20Al%20Faisal's%20speech%20at%20a%20US%20university%20also%20mentions%20India%20when%20he%20cites%20the%20example%20of%20the%20Independence%20movement%20as%20an%20example%20of%20resisting%20occupation%20through%20civil%20disobedience.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20viral%20video%20of%20the%20address%20starts%20with%20the%2078-year-old%20saying%20that%20all%20occupied%20people%20have%20a%20right%20to%20resist%20their%20occupation%2C%20even%20militarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20support%20the%20military%20option%20in%20Palestine.%20I%20prefer%20the%20other%20option%3A%20civil%20insurrection%20and%20disobedience.%20It%20brought%20down%20the%20British%20empire%20in%20India%20and%20the%20Soviet%20empire%20in%20eastern%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHis%20Royal%20Highness%20Prince%20Turki%20Al%20Faisal%20Al%20Saud%2C%20former%20Ambassador%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20the%20U.S.%2C%20gives%20his%20perspective.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FBakerLive%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23BakerLive%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FmRwYiCqTkG%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FmRwYiCqTkG%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Baker%20Institute%20(%40BakerInstitute)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBakerInstitute%2Fstatus%2F1714318809245389143%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2017%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%2C%20he%20said%2C%20has%20overwhelming%20military%20superiority%20and%20the%20world%20can%20see%20the%20devastation%20it%20is%20causing%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHitting%20out%20at%20Hamas%20for%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20that%20sparked%20the%20war%2C%20Faisal%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20categorically%20condemn%20Hamas'%20targeting%20of%20civilian%20targets%20of%20any%20age%20or%20gender%20as%20it%20is%20accused%20of.%20Such%20targeting%20belies%20Hamas'%20claims%20to%20an%20Islamic%20identity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20Islamic%20injunctions%2C%20he%20said%2C%20against%20the%20killing%20of%20innocent%20children%20and%20women%20and%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20against%20desecration%20of%20places%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas'%20surprise%20attacks%20on%20Israel%20cities%20and%20the%20brutal%20retaliation%20have%20claimed%20over%205%2C800%20lives%20so%20far%2C%20according%20to%20UN%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Saudi%20prince%20slammed%20Hamas%20for%20%26quot%3Bgifting%20the%20high%20moral%20ground%20to%20an%20Israeli%20government%20that%20is%20universally%20shunned%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BI%20condemn%20Hamas%20for%20giving%20this%20awful%20government%20the%20excuse%20to%20ethnically%20cleanse%20Gaza%20of%20its%20citizens%20and%20bombing%20them%20to%20oblivion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Saudi%20prince%20also%20slammed%20Hamas%20for%20sabotaging%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20attempt%20to%20reach%20a%20peaceful%20resolution%20to%20the%20Palestine%20issue.%20Multiple%20experts%20have%20said%20the%20normalisation%20of%20Israel-Saudi%20Arabia%20relations%2C%20which%20was%20paused%20due%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20was%20a%20crucial%20backdrop%20against%20which%20Hamas%20planned%20its%20unprecedented%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Saudi%20prince%20minced%20no%20words%20in%20his%20criticism%20of%20Israel%20for%20its%20counterstrike%20that%20targeted%20innocent%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20and%20West%20Bank.%20%26quot%3BTwo%20wrongs%20don't%20make%20a%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECountering%20the%20US%20media's%20use%20of%20%26quot%3Bunprovoked%20attack%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20Hamas'%20offensive%20in%20Israel%2C%20Faisal%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20more%20provocation%20is%20required%20to%20make%20it%20provoked%20than%20what%20Israel%20has%20done%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20for%20three-quarters%20of%20a%20century%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFlagging%20Israel's%20alleged%20excesses%20in%20Palestine%20and%20the%20killing%20of%20civilians%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20bloodletting%20must%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20condemn%20Israel's%20stealing%20of%20Palestinian%20lands%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20further%20accusing%20Tel%20Aviv%20of%20targeted%20killings%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20jailing%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Saudi%20prince%20also%20hit%20out%20at%20Western%20politicians%20for%20%26quot%3Bshedding%20tears%26quot%3B%20when%20Israelis%20are%20killed%20by%20Palestinians%20but%20%26quot%3Brefusing%20to%20even%20express%20sorrow%26quot%3B%20when%20it's%20the%20other%20way%20around.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20heroes%20in%20this%20conflict%2C%20only%20victims%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFaisal%20led%20the%20Saudi%20intelligence%20agency%20Al%20Mukhabarat%20Al%20'Ammah%20for%2024%20years%20and%20also%20served%20as%20the%20country's%20ambassador%20to%20London%20and%20the%20US.%20While%20he%20does%20not%20hold%20any%20public%20office%20at%20this%20point%2C%20it%20is%20unl