%20each%20and%20every%20district%20of%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20approach%20of%20building%20new%20water%20bodies%2C%20dams%20and%20canals%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20ecologically%20and%20environmentally%20damaging%20and%20often%20leads%20to%20large%20scale%20displacement%20of%20the%20locals%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20500%20water%20bodies%20were%20rejuvenated%20with%20financial%20support%20from%20NITI%20Aayog.%20Currently%2C%20pilot%20projects%20are%20ongoing%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20MP%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20with%20a%20view%20to%20extending%20this%20to%20all%20its%20aspirational%20districts%20and%20regions%20that%20are%20water%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20614px)%20100vw%2C%20614px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253.jpeg%20614w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-500x281.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-150x84.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332699%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaharashtra%20goes%20all%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%2050%20years%2C%20droughts%20and%20floods%20in%20Maharashtra%20have%20risen%20sevenfold%20and%20sixfold%20respectively.%20It%20was%20after%20the%20latest%20devastating%20droughts%20faced%20by%20the%20state%20in%202013-2016%20that%20the%20state%20intensified%20its%20efforts%20on%20making%20defunct%20water%20bodies%20functional.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20rejuvenated%20over%205%2C000%20water%20bodies%20across%20the%20state%20between%202017-2019%2C%20mostly%20through%20the%20GDGS%20(Gaalmukt%20Dharan%2C%20Gaalmukt%20Shivar)%20Scheme.%20At%20this%20time%2C%20donors%20were%20providing%20the%20rental%20charges%20for%20the%20machines%20for%20silt%20removal%2C%20the%20state%20paid%20for%20the%20diesel%20and%20the%20farmers%20for%20the%20carting%20of%20silt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20recently%2C%20faced%20with%20the%20threat%20of%20El%20Nino%20and%20erratic%20rain%20patterns%2C%20the%20state%20decided%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20wait%20for%20donors%20or%20other%20philanthropic%20funding%20and%20that%20it%20would%20fund%20the%20full%20effort%20on%20its%20own%20steam%20for%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20were%20allocated%20to%20revive%20the%20scheme%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20and%20over%20100%20NGOs%20were%20pulled%20in%20to%20assist.%20It%20is%20expected%20to%20lead%20to%20the%20excavation%20of%20around%2044%20crore%20cubic%20metres%20of%20silt%20and%20creating%20an%20additional%20surface%20capacity%20of%2044%2C000%20crore%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F295019%2Fkarnataka-couple-runs-ngo-anisha-help-farmers-switch-to-organic-farmer-in-drought-prone-district%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elitres%20of%20water%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20a%20subsidy%20of%20Rs%2015%2C000%20has%20been%20provided%20for%20small%20farmers%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20silt%20can%20be%20used%20by%20them%20as%20well%20as%20the%20bigger%20farmers%20who%20can%20afford%20to%20cart%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20777px)%20100vw%2C%20777px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20April%202023%2C%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20were%20allocated%20to%20revive%20the%20scheme%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20and%20over%20100%20NGOs%20were%20pulled%20in%20to%20assist.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292.jpg%20777w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292-768x512.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F9C20E46F-29E0-4BF4-B138-BC5D6BD19FE6_11zon-1697802292-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332702%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20were%20allocated%20to%20revive%20the%20scheme%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20and%20over%20100%20NGOs%20were%20pulled%20in%20to%20assist.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIt%20takes%20two%20hands%20to%20clap%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EReaders%20may%20well%20ask%20what%20the%20civil%20society%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20is%20in%20cases%20where%20the%20entire%20funding%20is%20provided%20by%20the%20government.%20And%20the%20answer%20is%20%E2%80%93%20it%20takes%20both%20hands%20to%20clap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20has%20been%20seen%20time%20and%20again%2C%20the%20projects%20that%20work%20best%20are%20those%20where%20the%20private%20and%20public%20sector%20come%20together%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20a%20former%20NITI%20Aayog%20official.%20He%20says%20that%20the%20private%20or%20civil%20society%20players%20bring%20efficiencies%20and%20levels%20of%20competence%20that%20government%20players%20often%20lack.%20Chandra%20echoes%20this%20sentiment%20in%20reverse%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20scale%20government%20can%20provide%2C%20no%20private%20sector%20player%20can%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20even%20while%20the%20state%20government%20is%20willing%20to%20finance%20almost%20the%20entire%20effort%2C%20the%20A.T.E.%20CF%20identifies%2C%20monitors%20and%20assists%20the%20NGOs%20that%20work%20on%20the%20ground.%20It%20has%20also%20lent%20its%20technology%20app%20to%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20to%20collect%20real%20time%20data%20on%20all%20the%20water%20rejuvenation%20sites%20across%20the%20state%20from%20the%20Mantralaya%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20to%20prioritise%20where%20such%20work%20needs%20to%20commence%20right%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20foundation%20also%20provides%20regular%20weekly%20training%20for%20the%20nodal%20government%20officers%20with%20use%20of%20the%20app%20and%20any%20glitches%20that%20may%20arise.%20Besides%20setting%20up%20a%20project%20management%20unit%2C%20the%20foundation%E2%80%99s%20chief%20operating%20officer%20(COO)%20Gayatri%20Nair%20Lobo%2C%20has%20made%2024%20field%20trips%20to%20six%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Karnataka%20since%20April%202022%20alone.%20In%20a%20country%20as%20vast%2C%20diverse%20and%20complex%20as%20India%2C%20very%20little%20can%20be%20achieved%20from%20the%20glass%20and%20chrome%20edifices%20in%20Mumbai%20or%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Nutanben%20and%20her%208-10%20member%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F276231%2Fpune-engineer-helps-maharashtra-villages-become-drought-free-water-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteam%20remain%20resolutely%20focussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20work%20which%20they%20estimate%20will%20need%20another%202-3%20years%20before%20it%20becomes%20self-sustaining.%20She%20knows%20her%20frequent%20trips%20from%20Mumbai%20to%20Aurangabad%20and%20then%20onwards%20into%20the%20nooks%20and%20crannies%20of%20Jalna%20and%20Palghar%20will%20not%20be%20ending%20anytime%20in%20a%20hurry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20filial%20responsibilities%20less%20intense%20than%20in%20the%20past%2C%20she%20can%20afford%20to%20focus%20on%20ameliorating%20the%20water%20woes%20she%20first%20encountered%20when%20she%20landed%20in%20Beed%20seven%20years%20ago.%20In%20terms%20of%20gratification%2C%20anything%20she%20achieves%20in%20Mumbai%20pales%20in%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWritten%20by%20Anjuli%20Bhargava.%20Anjuli%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20columnist%20based%20out%20of%20Goa%20and%20writes%20on%20business%20and%20social%20sector%20issues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E